/* Help Tabs */
//Add Item Instructions
1. Make sure you have selected proper group. To see how to select active group see help on Select Active Group. \n\n2. Select Items tab from Dashboard
3. Click on Add Button
4. Enter all details of the product. \n\nNote: If Category already exists, item will be added to that category. Otherwise new category will be created \n\nAdd Barcode using Camera Button \n\nAdd Location using Location Button \n\nClick Save Button to add the product.
//Delete Item Instructions
1. Select Items tab from the Dashboard. \n\n2. Click on item you want to delete. It will open Item Description \n\n3. Click on Delete Button To delete item.
//Delete Category Instructions
1. Select Items tab from the Dashboard. \n\n2. Click and hold on the category you want to delete. \n\n3. Click on Delete in the alert box to delete the category.
//Add Group Instructions
1. Select Groups tab on Main Screen. \n\n2. Click on Add Button at Right Bottom corner.
3. In the dialog box, enter name of group you want to create and hit Create Group button.
//Add Member Instructions
1. Select Groups tab on Main Screen. \n\n2. Click on group in which you want to add member. \n\n3. Click on Add Button at Right Bottom Corner.
4. In the dialog box, enter Phone Number of member you want to add in group and hit Add Member button.
//Accept Invitation Instructions
1. Select Groups tab on Main Screen. \n\n2. Click on Invitations
3. From the list of invitations, click on Accept Button to accept the invitation and get added in the group.
//Select Active Group Instructions
1. Click on 3 Horizontal Lines at Top Left corner.
2. In the Drawer, Select the group to set active from the Drop down. \n\n Note: Once you change the group, the data of the application will be change according to currently active group.
//Remove Item from Low Stock Instructions
1. Select Low Stock tab from Dashboard.
2. Click on Remove Icon of item you want to Mark as In Stock i.e. remove from Low Stock
//Add Item to Low Stock Instructions
1. Select Low Stock tab from Dashboard.
2. Click on Add Icon on Right Bottom corner
3. Click on Add Icon of item you want to Mark as Low Stock i.e. add to Low Stock
//Edit Name Instructions
1. Click on 3 Horizontal Lines at Top Left corner.
2. Click on Edit Name option.
3. Enter new name and hit Change Name Button.
//Change Password Instructions
1. Click on 3 Horizontal Lines at Top Left corner.
2. Click on Change Password option.
3. Enter Current Password, New Password and Retype New Password.
